    "Next, digital captures from cervicography and hysteroscopic video clips come with poor quality due to blur, incomplete cervix or uterus exposure, lesions coated by vaginal discharge, heavy bleeding, and so forth (Yuan et al. 2020), resulting in a loss of clinically relevant features and a pronounced class imbalance.",
